quran[58]{c,v,t}:
  37,145,Then We cast him on to the desert shore while he was sick
  37,146,And We caused a gourd plant to grow above him
  37,147,And We sent him to a hundred thousand folk or more
  37,148,"And they believed; therefore, We gave them provision for a time"
  37,149,Now ask them (O Muhammad) has your Lord daughters while they have sons
  37,150,Or did We create the angels females while they were witnesses
  37,151,"Verily, it is of their own lies that they say"
  37,152,"Allah has begotten\"; and most surely they are liars"
  37,153,Has He chosen daughters in preference to sons
  37,154,"What ails you, how is it that you judge"
  37,155,Will you not then reflect
  37,156,Or have you a clear authority
  37,157,"Then bring your book (writ, record), if you are truthful"
  37,158,And they assert a relationship between Him and the Jinn; and certainly the Jinn do know that they shall surely be brought forth
  37,159,Glory be to Allah from all that they attribute (unto Him)
  37,160,"But not so the servants of Allah, the purified ones"
  37,161,So surely you and what you worship
  37,162,Cannot lead into temptation anyone against Him
  37,163,Save him who will go to hell
  37,164,"(The angels or those who are ranged in ranks say,) \"And there is none of us but has an assigned place"
  37,165,"Verily, we, even we, are they who draw out in ranks"
  37,166,"Verily, we, even we, are they who declare the glory (of Allah)"
  37,167,And there are those who used to say
  37,168,Had we a reminder from those of yore
  37,169,We would certainly have been the single-minded servants of Allah
  37,170,But (now that it is come) they disbelieve in it; but they will come to know
  37,171,And certainly Our word has already gone forth before this unto Our servants sent
  37,172,That most surely they shall be helped
  37,173,And most surely Our host alone shall be the victorious ones
  37,174,"Therefore, turn away from them till a time"
  37,175,"And watch, for they will soon come to see"
  37,176,What! Would they then hasten Our chastisement
  37,177,"But when it descends on them, evil will then be the morning for those who have been warned"
  37,178,And turn away from them for a time
  37,179,"And watch, for they will soon come to see"
  37,180,"Glorified be your Lord, the Lord of Majesty, above all that which they attribute (unto Him)"
  37,181,And peace be unto those who are sent
  37,182,"And all praise be to Allah, the Lord of the Worlds"
  38,1,"Sad. (I swear) By the Quran, full of Zikr (remembrance in reverence and praising Allah, admonition, reciting, teaching, giving the message)"
  38,2,Nay! But those who disbelieve are in self-exaltation (pride) and separatism (schism)
  38,3,"How many generations did We destroy before them, then they cried when there was no longer time to escape"
  38,4,"And they marvel that there has come to them a Warner from among themselves, and the disbelievers say: \"This is an enchanter, a liar"
  38,5,"What! Makes he a single God out of the many gods? A strange thing is this, to be sure"
  38,6,"And the leaders among them go about exhorting, \"Go and remain constant to your gods; for this is most surely a thing designed against you"
  38,7,We never heard of this in the former faith; this is nothing but an invention
  38,8,"Has the reminder been revealed to him alone from among us?\" Nay! They are in doubt as to My reminder. Nay! They have not yet tasted My chastisement"
  38,9,"Or is it that they have the treasures of the mercy of your Lord, the Mighty, the Bestower"
  38,10,Or is it that theirs is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and what is between them? Then let them ascend by ropes
  38,11,"But there they shall be put to flight, even as a confederated host"
  38,12,"The people of Noah before them denied the messengers and so did the people of A´ad, and Pharaoh, the Lord of Stakes (of stability)"
  38,13,And the people of Thamud and the people of Lot and the Companions of the Woods; these were the factions
  38,14,"There was none of them but denied the messengers, therefore, just was My retribution"
  38,15,"These wait aught but a single Shout, which brooks no delay"
  38,16,"And they say, \"Our Lord! Hasten on to us our portion before the Day of Reckoning"
  38,17,"Bear patiently what they say, and remember Our servant David, the possessor of power; surely he was frequent in turning (to Allah)"
  38,18,Surely We made the mountains sing the glory (of Allah) in unison with him at nightfall and sunrise
  38,19,And the birds gathered together; all joined in singing with him
  38,20,And We strengthened his kingdom and We gave him wisdom and a clear judgment